Lowvelders flocked to Yoons@Barnyard to watch the talented Jak de Priester on Friday night. Guests enjoyed a variety of drinks from the theatre’s bar and delicious pizzas made on-site by Yoons. After everybody had eaten and chatted, it was time for De Priester to take to the stage. Within minutes of starting his performance, he had the audience in stitches with his musical numbers and his amusing storytelling between sets. ALSO READ: A venture into the hidden Spekboom Valley with Mpumalanga Heritage experiencing The show had a successful turnout and was enjoyed by everybody. Not a single person left the theatre that night without having laughed. Laeveld Trekkers contributed to the show by providing block bookings to their clients for the performance and displayed a big blue tractor near the entrance. Do you have more information about the story? Please send us an email to editorial@lowvelder.co.za. For free breaking and community news, visit Lowvelder’s website: Lowvelder For more news and interesting articles, like Lowvelder on Facebook, follow us on Twitter or Instagram